{"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"anchor":"Overview","type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"While Gtk isn’t the preferred UI framework on every Linux distro, it’s the closest thing SwiftCrossUI has to a native Linux backend for now. The Qt backend may be brought back to life at some point to cover the rest of Linux distros.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For targetting older pre Gtk 4 Linux distros, see the secondary "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/Gtk3Backend","isActive":true}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This backend supports Linux, macOS, and Windows, but its support for macOS has a few known issues worse due to underlying Gtk issues (and its support for Windows isn’t well tested).","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"System-dependencies","type":"heading","text":"System dependencies","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Before you can use ","type":"text"},{"code":"GtkBackend","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" you must install the required system dependencies for your platform. Here are installation instructions tailored to each supported platform;","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Linux","type":"heading","text":"Linux","level":3},{"syntax":"sh","type":"codeListing","code":["# Debian-based distros","sudo apt install libgtk-4-dev clang","","# Fedora-based distros","sudo dnf install gtk4-devel clang"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Figure 1: "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"installing the required dependencies on Debian-based and Fedora-based Linux distros","type":"text"}]}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you run into errors related to not finding "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"gtk\/gtk.h"},{"type":"text","text":" when trying to build a swift-cross-ui project, try restarting your computer. This has worked in some cases (although there may be a more elegant solution)."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If you are on a non-Debian non-Fedora distro and the ","type":"text"},{"code":"GtkBackend","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" requirements end up differing significantly from the requirements stated above, please open a GitHub issue or PR so that we can improve the documentation.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"macOS","type":"heading","text":"macOS","level":3},{"syntax":"sh","type":"codeListing","code":["brew install pkg-config gtk4"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Figure 2: ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"installing the required dependencies using Homebrew","type":"text"}]}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you don’t have Homebrew, installation instructions can be found at "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/brew.sh","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It should also be possible to use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"gtk4"},{"type":"text","text":" installed via MacPorts, but I have not tested that."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you run into errors related to "},{"code":"libffi","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"code":"FFI","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" when trying to build a swift-cross-ui project with "},{"code":"GtkBackend","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", which can occur when certain older versions of the Xcode Command Line Tools are installed, try running the following command to patch libffi:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"sh","type":"codeListing","code":["sed -i '' 's\/-I..includedir.\/\/g' $(brew --prefix)\/Library\/Homebrew\/os\/mac\/pkgconfig\/*\/libffi.pc"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Figure 3: "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"fixing the ","type":"text"},{"code":"libffi","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" issue that some people face","type":"text"}]}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Windows","type":"heading","text":"Windows","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On Windows things are a bit complicated (as usual), so we only support installation via "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/microsoft\/vcpkg","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". First, install vcpkg;"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"sh","type":"codeListing","code":["git clone https:\/\/github.com\/microsoft\/vcpkg C:\\vcpkg","C:\\vcpkg\\bootstrap-vcpkg.bat"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Figure 4: ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"install vcpkg (requires git cli)"}]}],"type":"paragraph"},{"style":"warning","name":"Warning","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"It’s important to install vcpkg at the root of a drive due to limitations of the Gtk build system.","type":"text"}]}],"type":"aside"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"After installation, make the following changes to your environment variables:","type":"text"}]}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Set the ","type":"text"},{"code":"PKG_CONFIG_PATH","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" environment variable to ","type":"text"},{"code":"C:\\vcpkg\\installed\\x64-windows\\lib\\pkgconfig","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". This is only required for building.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Add ","type":"text"},{"code":"C:\\vcpkg\\installed\\x64-windows\\bin","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to your ","type":"text"},{"code":"Path","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" environment variable. This is only required for running.","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"With vcpkg installed, you have two options for Gtk installation; global installation, and project-local installation"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Global-Gtk-4-installation-recommended","type":"heading","text":"Global Gtk 4 installation (recommended)","level":4},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that the command depends on your machine’s architecture; choose between Figure 5 and Figure 6 accordingly."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Installation can take 45+ minutes depending on your machine."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"sh","type":"codeListing","code":["C:\\vcpkg\\vcpkg.exe install gtk --triplet x64-windows"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Figure 5: ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"install Gtk 4 globally on x64 Windows"}],"type":"emphasis"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"sh","type":"codeListing","code":["C:\\vcpkg\\vcpkg.exe install gtk --triplet arm64-windows"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Figure 6: "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"install Gtk 4 globally on arm64 Windows","type":"text"}]}],"type":"paragraph"},{"style":"warning","name":"Warning","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Run the chosen command at the root of your drive to ensure that vcpkg doesn’t run in manifest mode."}]}],"type":"aside"},{"anchor":"Project-local-Gtk-4-installation-more-unreliable","type":"heading","text":"Project-local Gtk 4 installation (more unreliable)","level":4},{"style":"note","name":"Note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If the absolute path to your project contains spaces, it is possible that vcpkg will break, and installing globally will be a more reliable strategy."}]}],"type":"aside"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To install Gtk 4 in a project-local dependency store you must setup a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"vcpkg.json"},{"type":"text","text":" manifest file and then run vcpkg, as detailed below;"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"First "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"vcpkg.json"},{"type":"text","text":" at the root of your project and make sure that it includes the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"gtk"},{"type":"text","text":" dependency as demonstrated in Figure 7."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"json","type":"codeListing","code":["{","    \"name\": \"project-name\",","    \"version-string\": \"main\",","    \"dependencies\": [\"gtk\"]","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Figure 7: "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"an example "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"vcpkg.json"},{"type":"text","text":" package manifest"}]}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"sh","type":"codeListing","code":["C:\\vcpkg\\vcpkg.exe install --triplet x64-windows"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Figure 8: "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"install the dependencies listed in your package manifest","type":"text"}]}],"type":"paragraph"},{"style":"warning","name":"Warning","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Replace the triplet with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"arm64-windows"},{"type":"text","text":" if you’re on ARM64"}]}],"type":"aside"},{"anchor":"Usage","type":"heading","text":"Usage","level":2},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["...","","let package = Package(","  ...","  targets: [","    ...","    .executableTarget(","      name: \"YourApp\",","      dependencies: [","        .product(name: \"SwiftCrossUI\", package: \"swift-cross-ui\"),","        .product(name: \"GtkBackend\", package: \"swift-cross-ui\"),","      ]","    )","    ...","  ]","  ...",")"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Figure 9: "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"adding ","type":"text"},{"code":"GtkBackend","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to an executable target","type":"text"}]}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["import SwiftCrossUI","import GtkBackend","","@main","struct YourApp: App {","  \/\/ You can explicitly initialize your app's chosen backend if you desire.","  \/\/ This happens automatically when you import any of the built-in backends.","  \/\/","  \/\/ var backend = GtkBackend()","  \/\/","  \/\/ If you aren't using Swift Bundler, you may have to explicitly provide","  \/\/ your app's identifier for some GtkBackend features to work correctly","  \/\/ (such as handling custom URL schemes).","  \/\/","  \/\/ var backend = GtkBackend(appIdentifier: \"com.example.YourApp\")","","  var body: some Scene {","    WindowGroup {","      Text(\"Hello, World!\")","        .padding()","    }","  }","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Figure 10: "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"using "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkBackend"}],"type":"emphasis"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"abstract":[{"text":"SwiftCrossUI’s native Linux backend built on top of Gtk 4.","type":"text"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftcrossui\/gtkbackend"]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/GtkBackend"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI","doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/Built-in-backends"]]},"metadata":{"title":"GtkBackend","role":"article","modules":[{"name":"SwiftCrossUI"}],"roleHeading":"Article"},"sections":[],"kind":"article","seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/DefaultBackend","doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/AppKitBackend","doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/UIKitBackend","doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/WinUIBackend","doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/Gtk3Backend"],"generated":true}],"references":{"doc://SwiftCrossUI/documentation/SwiftCrossUI/WinUIBackend":{"type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"SwiftCrossUI’s native Windows backend built on top of WinUI 3.","type":"text"}],"role":"article","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/swiftcrossui\/winuibackend","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/WinUIBackend","title":"WinUIBackend"},"doc://SwiftCrossUI/documentation/SwiftCrossUI/UIKitBackend":{"kind":"article","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/UIKitBackend","title":"UIKitBackend","abstract":[{"text":"SwiftCrossUI’s native iOS and tvOS backend built on top of UIKit.","type":"text"}],"role":"article","url":"\/documentation\/swiftcrossui\/uikitbackend"},"https://github.com/microsoft/vcpkg":{"url":"https:\/\/github.com\/microsoft\/vcpkg","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/microsoft\/vcpkg","title":"vcpkg","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"vcpkg","type":"text"}],"type":"link"},"https://brew.sh":{"url":"https:\/\/brew.sh","identifier":"https:\/\/brew.sh","title":"brew.sh","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"brew.sh","type":"text"}],"type":"link"},"doc://SwiftCrossUI/documentation/SwiftCrossUI/AppKitBackend":{"role":"article","url":"\/documentation\/swiftcrossui\/appkitbackend","kind":"article","abstract":[{"text":"SwiftCrossUI’s native macOS backend built on top of AppKit.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/AppKitBackend","title":"AppKitBackend","type":"topic"},"doc://SwiftCrossUI/documentation/SwiftCrossUI/Built-in-backends":{"kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/Built-in-backends","title":"Built-in backends","url":"\/documentation\/swiftcrossui\/built-in-backends","role":"collectionGroup","type":"topic","abstract":[]},"doc://SwiftCrossUI/documentation/SwiftCrossUI/DefaultBackend":{"kind":"article","title":"DefaultBackend","url":"\/documentation\/swiftcrossui\/defaultbackend","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/DefaultBackend","role":"article","abstract":[{"text":"An adaptive backend which uses different backends under the hood depending on the target operating system.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic"},"doc://SwiftCrossUI/documentation/SwiftCrossUI":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI","url":"\/documentation\/swiftcrossui","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Create cross-platform desktop apps for macOS, Linux, Windows, iOS and tvOS."}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","role":"collection","title":"SwiftCrossUI"},"doc://SwiftCrossUI/documentation/SwiftCrossUI/Gtk3Backend":{"title":"Gtk3Backend","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/Gtk3Backend","url":"\/documentation\/swiftcrossui\/gtk3backend","type":"topic","kind":"article","role":"article","abstract":[{"text":"A secondary Linux backend built on top of Gtk 3 (for older distros without Gtk 4).","type":"text"}]}}}